        <h3 class="sub-title">Understanding Investment Risks</h3>
        <p class="sub-lead" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Every investment carries risk. Understanding these risks helps you invest with clarity and avoid common mistakes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="risks">
        <div class="risk"><h4>Market Risk</h4><p>Equity markets are influenced by economic conditions, interest rate movements, inflation, policy changes, and global events. These factors can impact overall market performance, regardless of an individual company's fundamentals.</p></div>
        <div class="risk"><h4>Volatility Risk</h4><p>Stock prices may fluctuate significantly in the short term, leading to temporary gains or losses. While volatility is a natural part of equity investing, it may lead to temporary declines in portfolio value.</p></div>
        <div class="risk"><h4>Company-Specific Risk</h4><p>Business challenges, management issues, or regulatory changes can affect the performance of individual stocks. Investing heavily in a single stock can increase exposure to company-specific risks.</p></div>
        <div class="risk"><h4>Behavioural Risk</h4><p>Emotional decisions such as panic selling or chasing market trends can negatively impact long-term returns. Maintaining a disciplined investment approach is essential for wealth creation.</p></div>
      </div>
